We have translated two of his books

00:00:34.660 --> 00:00:35.800
into Russian, “Concept of

00:00:35.800 --> 00:00:37.900
Controlling” and “Implementation

00:00:37.900 --> 00:00:40.520
of a Balanced System of Indicators”.

00:00:40.520 --> 00:00:44.240
The structure of our course on this slide.

00:00:44.460 --> 00:00:46.920
First, we will talk about the location

00:00:46.920 --> 00:00:48.360
of management accounting in the control

00:00:48.360 --> 00:00:51.820
system, then compare the three

00:00:51.820 --> 00:00:53.120
accounts that, as a rule, the

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:53.900
company has.

00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:56.400
This is the tax that companies

00:00:56.400 --> 00:00:58.740
conduct to provide information

00:00:58.740 --> 00:01:00.820
to government agencies.

00:01:00.820 --> 00:01:03.120
These are the financial ones that companies

00:01:03.120 --> 00:01:05.800
run to provide information to the

00:01:05.800 --> 00:01:09.120
capital market, banks, exchanges and so on.

00:01:09.240 --> 00:01:10.820
And we'll talk about the management

00:01:10.820 --> 00:01:12.880
accounting that companies keep for themselves

00:01:12.880 --> 00:01:14.960
to understand what's really

00:01:14.960 --> 00:01:16.860
happening in the business.

00:01:17.680 --> 00:01:19.680
The next point of our course is key

00:01:19.680 --> 00:01:21.240
performance indicators, so-called KPIs,

00:01:21.300 --> 00:01:23.220
key performance indicators,

00:01:23.220 --> 00:01:25.360
that is, these are the bulbs

00:01:25.360 --> 00:01:26.940
that usually light on the plane

00:01:26.940 --> 00:01:32.740
or manager if you compare the

00:01:32.940 --> 00:01:34.560
manager to the pilot of

00:01:34.560 --> 00:01:35.940
the aircraft.

00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:38.280
Furthermore, management reports

00:01:38.280 --> 00:01:41.460
are reports that we receive in

00:01:41.460 --> 00:01:42.920
addition to indicators to understand

00:01:42.920 --> 00:01:44.460
what is happening in

00:01:44.460 --> 00:01:46.420
the business.

00:01:48.180 --> 00:01:49.880
In tax and financial accounting, external

00:01:49.880 --> 00:01:51.400
users are interested in the outcome

00:01:51.400 --> 00:01:53.980
of the business as a whole, but in management

00:01:54.080 --> 00:01:55.320
accounting we are interested in

00:01:55.320 --> 00:01:57.580
the efficiency of the work of not only

00:01:57.580 --> 00:01:59.580
the company as a whole, but

00:01:59.580 --> 00:02:01.080
also individual structural units.

00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:02.960
In the next paragraph we talk about the

00:02:02.960 --> 00:02:06.620
financial structure, about the centers

00:02:06.620 --> 00:02:07.960
of financial responsibility.

00:02:08.320 --> 00:02:09.620
It is the structural unit of the

00:02:09.620 --> 00:02:12.460
company responsible for one or another

00:02:12.460 --> 00:02:14.640
part of the profit and loss report.

00:02:14.840 --> 00:02:16.760
There are structural units that

00:02:16.780 --> 00:02:19.380
are solely responsible for costs.

00:02:19.460 --> 00:02:20.920
But since some structural

00:02:20.920 --> 00:02:22.380
units, in addition to costs, also

00:02:22.380 --> 00:02:26.320
generate income, structural units

00:02:26.320 --> 00:02:31.020
are either designated as centers

00:02:31.020 --> 00:02:32.440
of gross income or as centers

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:33.380
of profit.

00:02:33.700 --> 00:02:35.040
In addition, within this point, a

00:02:35.040 --> 00:02:37.340
very interesting topic is

00:02:37.340 --> 00:02:39.000
domestic prices, or so-called

00:02:39.000 --> 00:02:40.240
transfer prices.

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:43.060
This is the price at which

00:02:43.060 --> 00:02:44.760
a product or service within

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:46.360
the company moves from one division

00:02:46.360 --> 00:02:48.800
to another.

00:02:49.600 --> 00:02:50.960
The next item of the program is

00:02:50.960 --> 00:02:52.480
the accounting policy of management

00:02:52.480 --> 00:02:54.280
accounting, that is, these are

00:02:54.680 --> 00:02:56.920
the rules, principles, canons

00:02:56.920 --> 00:02:59.020
that we must observe within

00:02:59.020 --> 00:03:00.660
the company, verified by internal

00:03:00.660 --> 00:03:04.260
audit, so that the figures

00:03:04.260 --> 00:03:05.500
we can trust are obtained in

00:03:05.500 --> 00:03:07.260
the reports.

00:03:07.380 --> 00:03:09.760
The last item of the program

00:03:09.760 --> 00:03:12.040
is the plan of management accounts.

00:03:13.120 --> 00:03:15.400
The last point of the program

00:03:15.400 --> 00:03:17.020
is some organizational aspects.

00:03:17.020 --> 00:03:18.100
As part of this paragraph,

00:03:18.100 --> 00:03:20.980
we will talk about how to organize

00:03:20.980 --> 00:03:22.420
management accounting in the company,

00:03:22.420 --> 00:03:24.720
who it is most concerned, who

00:03:24.720 --> 00:03:26.640
in the smaller, how different

00:03:26.660 --> 00:03:28.440
structural units are

00:03:28.440 --> 00:03:31.620
involved in this process and

00:03:31.620 --> 00:03:36.220
can how it eventually connects

00:03:36.220 --> 00:03:39.280
with each other and how it

00:03:39.280 --> 00:03:41.080
ends up being used blindly

00:03:41.080 --> 00:03:42.060
on the table.

00:03:48.050 --> 00:03:50.470
Management accounting as a system

00:03:50.470 --> 00:03:53.510
is part of an integrated

00:03:53.510 --> 00:03:55.370
concept called controlling

00:03:55.370 --> 00:03:57.030
in Germany.

00:03:57.030 --> 00:03:59.110
And what it is, I will try

00:03:59.110 --> 00:04:01.210
to explain to you by an example

00:04:01.210 --> 00:04:03.190
of how two people, husband

00:04:03.190 --> 00:04:04.510
and wife, go on holiday.

00:04:04.750 --> 00:04:07.790
Imagine that before going on vacation,

00:04:07.790 --> 00:04:09.250
a husband asks his wife, dear,

00:04:09.570 --> 00:04:11.750
what goals we set before us

00:04:11.750 --> 00:04:13.170
when going on vacation.

00:04:13.790 --> 00:04:14.990
My wife says to rest.

00:04:15.890 --> 00:04:18.970
And the husband, more skilled in the field

00:04:18.970 --> 00:04:20.450
of control, says the wife, the goal

00:04:20.450 --> 00:04:21.410
is not formulated quite

00:04:21.410 --> 00:04:24.810
correctly, the goal should

00:04:24.810 --> 00:04:25.450
be measurable.

00:04:25.950 --> 00:04:27.890
So, the goal is

00:04:27.890 --> 00:04:31.790
to rest at 100%.

00:04:35.980 --> 00:04:37.620
So the goal of these two people

00:04:37.640 --> 00:04:39.380
who go on vacation is to rest at

00:04:39.520 --> 00:04:42.660
100%, and this is the scale by which

00:04:42.660 --> 00:04:46.560
they will monitor the degree of

00:04:46.560 --> 00:04:47.660
rest during the vacation

00:04:47.660 --> 00:04:49.940
– 25%, 50%, 75% of the degree So, control

00:04:49.940 --> 00:04:57.560
starts with the setting of a goal,

00:04:58.520 --> 00:05:00.200
with the development of some

00:05:00.200 --> 00:05:02.920
measurable goals, and the second

00:05:02.920 --> 00:05:06.640
stage – is the allocation of the

00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:08.280
budget, the allocation of those

00:05:08.280 --> 00:05:09.880
resources that are necessary

00:05:09.880 --> 00:05:11.900
for us to the goals.

00:05:12.900 --> 00:05:14.260
So, the husband asks his

00:05:14.700 --> 00:05:16.160
wife, somehow you think how much

00:05:16.160 --> 00:05:17.960
money we will need to

00:05:17.960 --> 00:05:20.200
rest at 100%.

00:05:20.220 --> 00:05:22.500
My wife says, I think that

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:24.600
3500 euros for two is more or

00:05:24.600 --> 00:05:25.220
less real.

00:05:27.060 --> 00:05:30.100
The husband agrees they write this amount

00:05:30.100 --> 00:05:35.780
of 3500 euros for two and for now it

00:05:35.780 --> 00:05:37.040
is only a prediction of how much

00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:38.920
not in the holiday will spend but to

00:05:38.920 --> 00:05:42.040
turn it into a budget the husband takes

00:05:42.040 --> 00:05:43.800
a needle and pierces his wife's finger

00:05:43.800 --> 00:05:50.180
with a needle, so the signed

00:05:57.700 --> 00:05:59.420
blood forecast turns into

00:05:59.420 --> 00:06:03.300
a budget of 3500 euros for two and

00:06:03.300 --> 00:06:07.400
the goal is to rest at 100%.

00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:09.720
After that, management accounting

00:06:09.720 --> 00:06:10.880
begins, that is, the collection

00:06:10.880 --> 00:06:13.560
of information on the fact.

00:06:13.560 --> 00:06:15.180
Information is collected in fact

00:06:15.180 --> 00:06:17.220
during the control cuts.

00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:19.220
The husband makes the first check-

00:06:19.220 --> 00:06:23.460
in cut after 3 days of vacation.

00:06:23.460 --> 00:06:25.560
He makes the first check-in

00:06:26.490 --> 00:06:29.090
and asks his wife how restful

00:06:29.090 --> 00:06:30.710
you are at the moment.

00:06:31.370 --> 00:06:32.990
My wife says that the feelings

00:06:32.990 --> 00:06:34.650
are strange enough, only 3 days

00:06:34.650 --> 00:06:36.230
in vacation, and already 80

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:38.690
percent, I feel rested.

00:06:39.230 --> 00:06:40.350
And my husband says, you know,

00:06:40.350 --> 00:06:41.870
I have the same feelings,

00:06:41.870 --> 00:06:44.710
I also feel 80 percent rested.

00:06:45.050 --> 00:06:47.750
We can draw a line like this,

00:06:47.750 --> 00:06:54.730
this is how the resting curve behaves.

00:06:55.670 --> 00:06:58.390
By the end of the third day, the rate

00:06:58.390 --> 00:07:00.870
of achieving the goal is 80%.

00:07:00.870 --> 00:07:02.810
The husband has a laptop, flash drive,

00:07:02.850 --> 00:07:05.070
exel with him on vacation, and he

00:07:05.070 --> 00:07:07.050
records exactly the amount spent,

00:07:07.050 --> 00:07:08.810
how much they spent on restaurants,

00:07:08.810 --> 00:07:10.290
how much they spent on

00:07:10.290 --> 00:07:12.330
some other items.

00:07:12.330 --> 00:07:14.010
And by the end of the third

00:07:14.010 --> 00:07:16.750
day the amount is not very

00:07:16.750 --> 00:07:20.750
large - 200 euros.

00:07:22.140 --> 00:07:24.380
I remember what was initially discussed in the

00:07:24.380 --> 00:07:26.980
figure of 3,500 euros for the entire period

00:07:26.980 --> 00:07:29.540
and the goal is to rest at 100%.

00:07:29.540 --> 00:07:32.140
My husband has an interesting idea.

00:07:32.200 --> 00:07:33.720
He recalls the “20 to 80” principle

00:07:33.720 --> 00:07:36.040
and says, “Woman, what's the point?

00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:40.420
We have to spend another week and a

00:07:40.420 --> 00:07:42.800
half and spend 3,300 euros if we have

00:07:42.800 --> 00:07:48.360
already achieved the 80% of the goal we wanted.

00:07:48.640 --> 00:07:49.300
Go home to home.

00:07:50.000 --> 00:07:53.280
My wife says we wanted to rest

00:07:53.280 --> 00:07:55.020
at 100%, so I think we should

00:07:55.080 --> 00:07:56.580
stay and push out the

00:07:56.580 --> 00:07:59.440
remaining 20%.

00:07:59.440 --> 00:08:02.060
The husband agrees, and the

00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:03.640
second check cut he makes at the end

00:08:03.640 --> 00:08:07.920
of the first week, continuing

00:08:07.920 --> 00:08:09.000
to accumulate actual information,

00:08:09.000 --> 00:08:10.040
that is, essentially engaging

00:08:10.280 --> 00:08:14.640
in management By the end of the

00:08:14.640 --> 00:08:16.240
first week the actual rest rate

00:08:16.240 --> 00:08:19.620
of both holidaymakers is,

00:08:19.620 --> 00:08:24.220
say, 85%, it continued to

00:08:24.220 --> 00:08:26.320
grow and was 85% by the end

00:08:26.320 --> 00:08:29.540
of the first week.

00:08:30.220 --> 00:08:33.020
We look into a document called “Accounting

00:08:33.020 --> 00:08:34.420
for the Execution of the Budget”

00:08:34.420 --> 00:08:36.820
and in this document we find

00:08:36.820 --> 00:08:39.840
a number that is quite large,

00:08:39.840 --> 00:08:45.880
it is 3 thousand euros already.

00:08:48.200 --> 00:08:49.800
By the end of the first week, 3 thousand

00:08:49.800 --> 00:08:52.680
euros were spent out of a total of 3 500.

00:08:54.280 --> 00:08:56.640
The husband again offers to go

00:08:56.920 --> 00:08:58.840
home, because a very even

00:08:58.840 --> 00:09:01.260
good result, 85%, already

00:09:01.260 --> 00:09:02.140
spent a lot of money.

00:09:02.840 --> 00:09:04.460
In his view, it makes no

00:09:04.460 --> 00:09:06.500
sense to be on vacation for another

00:09:06.500 --> 00:09:09.040
whole week, for the remaining

00:09:09.040 --> 00:09:10.100
15% to rest, that is, it spends

00:09:10.100 --> 00:09:11.920
3,500.

00:09:12.040 --> 00:09:13.780
My wife says no, we wanted

00:09:13.780 --> 00:09:15.280
to rest at 100%, so I

00:09:15.280 --> 00:09:16.220
suggest staying.

00:09:16.660 --> 00:09:18.760
But, objectively evaluating the situation,

00:09:18.760 --> 00:09:21.280
I see that we cannot afford the

00:09:21.280 --> 00:09:25.080
remaining 15% for the remaining 500 euros.

00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:26.820
When we planned with you,

00:09:26.820 --> 00:09:28.020
we didn't know that in England,

00:09:28.020 --> 00:09:30.540
they went on vacation, such

00:09:30.540 --> 00:09:31.840
expensive football tickets, such

00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:33.420
expensive restaurants and all

00:09:33.420 --> 00:09:34.400
museums paid.

00:09:34.560 --> 00:09:36.520
We assumed that this was expensive,

00:09:36.520 --> 00:09:38.500
but thank God my husband had

00:09:38.500 --> 00:09:41.900
a reserve fund with him, and

00:09:41.900 --> 00:09:43.120
the newly adjusted

00:09:43.120 --> 00:09:45.340
newly approved budget value

00:09:45.340 --> 00:09:47.060
looks like this.

00:09:47.700 --> 00:09:54.740
Let's say 4 thousand euros, not in addition

00:09:55.040 --> 00:09:58.340
to that sum of 3,500, but only 4

00:09:58.340 --> 00:10:00.120
thousand, that is, 500 he added

00:10:00.120 --> 00:10:02.000
from the reserve fund.

00:10:02.660 --> 00:10:05.720
The third check-up took place three

00:10:05.720 --> 00:10:07.700
days later.

00:10:08.080 --> 00:10:10.240
The rest rate is 92%,

00:10:10.240 --> 00:10:16.500
the actual amount

00:10:16.500 --> 00:10:17.900
spent at this time,

00:10:17.900 --> 00:10:26.600
say, 3550 euros.

00:10:27.040 --> 00:10:28.800
The husband has not asked for home, he

00:10:28.800 --> 00:10:31.400
decided that we will be to the end,

00:10:31.400 --> 00:10:33.600
we will strive for the 100% achievement

00:10:33.600 --> 00:10:35.960
of the goals, and we will not re-

00:10:35.960 --> 00:10:37.260
examine the budget again.

00:10:38.920 --> 00:10:40.460
And the last fourth job

00:10:40.460 --> 00:10:42.280
is done by these two people

00:10:42.280 --> 00:10:43.640
after they return home.

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:45.100
This is the last fourth

00:10:45.100 --> 00:10:46.120
check.

00:10:48.360 --> 00:10:51.340
It turns out that the degree of rest

00:10:59.500 --> 00:11:00.420
when they are the actual

00:11:00.420 --> 00:11:10.400
amount spent was 3830 euros.

00:11:11.780 --> 00:11:14.740
In fact, the money spent is

00:11:14.740 --> 00:11:16.980
the actual degree of rest.

00:11:17.440 --> 00:11:19.880
We aimed at 100%, the original

00:11:19.880 --> 00:11:21.920
budget was 3500 euros, the

00:11:21.920 --> 00:11:23.800
adjusted budget was

00:11:24.140 --> 00:11:28.680
4 thousand euros, but in fact

00:11:28.680 --> 00:11:31.300
we spent 3830, controlling

00:11:31.300 --> 00:11:34.380
as a function suggests

00:11:34.380 --> 00:11:37.480
that we compare the actual

00:11:37.480 --> 00:11:39.080
degree of achievement with

00:11:39.080 --> 00:11:41.780
the plan and discuss why

00:11:41.780 --> 00:11:44.540
we still failed to rest 100%.

00:11:44.720 --> 00:11:46.480
98,5 percent is a good result, but

00:11:46.480 --> 00:11:48.100
still not 100%.

00:11:48.100 --> 00:11:51.000
And the second thing we compare is the

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:53.180
money actually spent with the plan,

00:11:53.180 --> 00:11:54.400
with the budget.

00:11:54.420 --> 00:11:55.820
We had two budgets, we discussed

00:11:55.820 --> 00:11:57.400
the deviations from that amount, from

00:11:57.400 --> 00:12:00.600
the first one that was signed with

00:12:00.600 --> 00:12:03.520
blood, when we did not know that

00:12:03.520 --> 00:12:06.180
restaurants were so expensive in England.

00:12:06.780 --> 00:12:08.900
We must compare this with the

00:12:08.900 --> 00:12:10.560
second value, with the adjusted

00:12:10.560 --> 00:12:11.940
budget value too, in order to discuss

00:12:12.080 --> 00:12:13.300
the deviations.

00:12:13.920 --> 00:12:16.380
The combination of these four actions

00:12:16.380 --> 00:12:19.300
- targeting, budgeting, control cuts,

00:12:19.720 --> 00:12:21.140
gathering information on the

00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:22.640
fact and identifying flights

00:12:22.640 --> 00:12:24.500
at the end, the fourth action,

00:12:24.500 --> 00:12:26.940
In the German and German

00:12:26.940 --> 00:12:28.380
business environments, the Anglo-

00:12:28.380 --> 00:12:31.680
Saxon term is usually called control.

00:12:32.400 --> 00:12:34.840
Management accounting is part of

00:12:34.840 --> 00:12:35.780
the control system.

00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:38.760
We've seen that this is the part where

00:12:38.760 --> 00:12:41.620
we actually collect information about

00:12:41.620 --> 00:12:43.280
the actual degree of achievement

00:12:43.280 --> 00:12:46.040
of goals and how the budget is executed.

00:12:47.340 --> 00:12:49.460
Within the framework of this program

